rComments: Probably the best prof at UTSC

He packs a lot of info into each lecture. A pure memorization based course. I would not recommend it as elective at all. The exam seems like it was made last minute, because the short answers questions were open ended and not specific. The tutorial is a waster of time, it does not supplement the lectures. The tutorial exams are very stressful.

Wants students to mention highly specific points for short answers that are open ended. Very specific multiple choice questions. Have to know species names for midterm and a lot less on the final. Midterm more difficult than final. Weekly assignments are free grades. MEGA tutorial test difficult due to time. Mesquite tutorial test was easy. gd prof

Prof Weir is very enthusiastic about the course material, knowledgeable, and all-around nice professor. The course was easily my favourite during my UTSC career. You are also taught useful statistical methods in the lab portion.
One of the best Biology profs at UTSC.  His lectures are amazing and he is very knowledgeable about evolutionary biology!
